filename: S01E16 The Two Parts Part I.txt
dialogue: Hi. Okay, will that be all?

filename: S01E16 The Two Parts Part I.txt
dialogue: Yeah, um, I was over there, then you said, "Excuse me, hello Miss," so now I’m here.

filename: S01E16 The Two Parts Part I.txt
dialogue: Right, yeah, ’cause its close to where I live, and the aprons are really cute.

filename: S01E16 The Two Parts Part I.txt
dialogue: Yeah, um, may we help you?
Hey!
Right, okay, the one that lives in Montuak, umm-hmm.
No, I umm, I read about her in Mom’s suicide note.
Yeah. So how have you been doing?
Well, it’s pretty much the gist. Well, except for the poem. You read the poem, right?
Umm, nothing. I mean, I’m getting married next week.
Wait! If umm, if you want to come, I guess that’d be okay.
Sure! Why not? You could be my sister for the day.
Huh. Well, I’m supposed to be working at the restaurant tonight. I’m supposed to be working right now, so who cares.
Hey!
Well they could be true.
Yeah, it’s a fine line huh?
I don’t know. He said he did all this stuff and then I said I did it too and he got so excited, it was really fun.
Y’know, we’d really better get going.
Hurry up I gotta pray!!
Who is it?
Hey!
No I’m not.
Yeah, can I help you with something?
Y’know, twin stuff is always a real big seller.
Yeah, I can talk them into giving you like, 30 dollars.
Right, why do you keep saying that?
Oh, it’s you.
Yeah, we’re not thirty, we’re 31.
Yea-huh! That’s what is says on my birth certificate.
Yeah, I got a big box of family stuff when my mom died.
No, I sold it to a Swedish runaway.
Yeah.
Yes.
Yes! Phoebe.
Right, okay, then no.

filename: S01E17 The Two Parts Part II.txt
dialogue: You have not changed!
Who is it?
Umm, yeah—no thanks.
Wow! Didn't she die like five years ago?
Okay, I know that I went to that all ready.
Well, then who's been dead for five years?
Umm, no. See I already thought she was dead so I kinda made my peace with it. Plus, I'm going to a concert tomorrow. So… I'd invite you, but umm, I only have two tickets left.
Thanks! Enjoy your funeral.
